description: APIs for capturing, analyzing, and embedding event data in everything you build.

blocks.name: createEvent
blocks.description: Records a single event to a given event collection.

blocks.name: createMultipleEvents
blocks.description: Record multiple events across one or more event collections.

blocks.name: getSingleEventCollection
blocks.description: Return schema information for a single event collection.

blocks.name: getAllCollections
blocks.description: Return schema information for all the event collections in a given project.

blocks.name: getSingleProperty
blocks.description: Return details for a single property in a given event collection.

blocks.name: getEventsCount
blocks.description: Return the number of events in the collection matching given criteria.

args.name: eventCollection
args.info: Specifies the name of the event collection to analyze.

args.name: timeframe
args.info: Limits analysis to a specific period of time when the events occurred.

blocks.name: getUniqueEventsCount
blocks.description: Return the number of events with unique values, for a target property in a collection matching given criteria. A common use for this is to count the number of unique users who performed an event.

args.name: eventCollection
args.info: Specifies the name of the event collection to analyze.

args.name: targetProperty
args.info: Specifies the name of the property to analyze.

args.name: timeframe
args.info: Limits analysis to a specific period of time when the events occurred.

blocks.name: getMinimumValue
blocks.description: Return the minimum numeric value for a target property, among all events in a collection matching given criteria.

args.name: eventCollection
args.info: Specifies the name of the event collection to analyze.

args.name: targetProperty
args.info: Specifies the name of the property to analyze.

args.name: timeframe
args.info: Limits analysis to a specific period of time when the events occurred.

blocks.name: getMaximunValue
blocks.description: Return the maximum numeric value for a target property, among all events in a collection matching given criteria.

args.name: eventCollection
args.info: Specifies the name of the event collection to analyze.

args.name: targetProperty
args.info: Specifies the name of the property to analyze.

args.name: timeframe
args.info: Limits analysis to a specific period of time when the events occurred.

blocks.name: calculatePropertyValues
blocks.description: Calculate the sum of all numeric values for a target property, among all events in a collection matching given criteria.

args.name: eventCollection
args.info: Specifies the name of the event collection to analyze.

args.name: targetProperty
args.info: Specifies the name of the property to analyze.

args.name: timeframe
args.info: Limits analysis to a specific period of time when the events occurred.

blocks.name: calculateAveragePropertyValues
blocks.description: Calculate the average value for a target property, among all events in a collection matching given criteria.

args.name: eventCollection
args.info: Specifies the name of the event collection to analyze.

args.name: targetProperty
args.info: Specifies the name of the property to analyze.

args.name: timeframe
args.info: Limits analysis to a specific period of time when the events occurred.

blocks.name: calculateMedianPropertyValues
blocks.description: Calculate the median value for a target property, among all events in a collection matching given criteria.

args.name: eventCollection
args.info: Specifies the name of the event collection to analyze.

args.name: targetProperty
args.info: Specifies the name of the property to analyze.

args.name: timeframe
args.info: Limits analysis to a specific period of time when the events occurred.

blocks.name: calculatePercentileValue
blocks.description: Calculate a specified percentile value for a target property, among all events in a collection matching given criteria.

args.name: eventCollection
args.info: Specifies the name of the event collection to analyze.

args.name: targetProperty
args.info: Specifies the name of the property to analyze.

args.name: timeframe
args.info: Limits analysis to a specific period of time when the events occurred.

args.name: percentile
args.info: Specifies the percentile to calculate, supporting 0-100 with two decimal places of precision. Example: 99.99.

blocks.name: getUniqueValues
blocks.description: Return a list of unique property values for a target property, among all events in a collection matching given criteria.

args.name: eventCollection
args.info: Specifies the name of the event collection to analyze.

args.name: targetProperty

args.name: timeframe
args.info: Limits analysis to a specific period of time when the events occurred.

args.name: query
args.info: Parameters for the query you want to save and have us run on an interval.

blocks.name: getSavedQueryResult
blocks.description: Getting Saved Query Results.

blocks.name: updateSavedQuery
blocks.description: To change the definition of the query, you must provide a complete new definition for the query in the “query” field in the body.

args.name: query
args.info: Parameters for the query you want to save and have us run on an interval.

args.name: queryName
args.info: Change the name of the query.

blocks.name: getAllSavedQueries
blocks.description: Getting All Saved Query Definitions.

args.name: queryName

blocks.name: createCachedQuery
blocks.description: By turning on caching, you can tell Keen to automatically refresh your saved queries so you can get immediate results. We will calculate the results of your query on a set interval, and have them available for you immediately when you ask for the Saved Query result.

args.name: queryName
args.info: Change the name of the query.

args.name: refreshRate
args.info: The refresh rate value is in seconds, and must be more than 1 hour (3,600 seconds) and less than 24 hours (86,400 seconds).

blocks.name: createCachedDataset
blocks.description: Create a Cached Dataset.

args.name: query
args.info: The query definition you want Keen to optimize for your application.

args.name: indexBy
args.info: The event property name of string values you will to retrieve results by; eg “product.id” stored as “1f2o3o4”, “5b6a7r8”. Currently supports one index_by property name. Cannot duplicate property query’s group_by.

args.name: displayName
args.info: The human-readable string name for your Cached Dataset

blocks.name: getSingleDataset
blocks.description: Getting a Dataset Definition.

blocks.name: getCachedDatasetResult
blocks.description: Retrieving results from a Cached Dataset.

args.name: indexBy
args.info: The string property value you want to retrieve results by.

args.name: timeframe
args.info: Limits retrieval of results to a specific portion of the Cached Dataset.

blocks.name: getProjectDatasets
blocks.description: Get list of Cached Dataset definitions for a project

args.name: limit
args.info: How many Cached Dataset definitions to return at a time (1-100). Defaults to 10.

args.name: afterName
args.info: A cursor for use in pagination. after_name is the Cached Dataset name that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 Cached Dataset definitions, ending with dataset_foo you can use dataset_foo as your after_name to retrieve the next page of definitions. Lists also return with helper “next_page_url” that uses after_name, so your subsequent call can fetch the next page of the list easily.

blocks.name: deleteCachedDataset
blocks.description: Delete a Cached Dataset.

blocks.name: getProjectQueries
blocks.description: Return a list of available query resources with a GET request.

blocks.name: createExtractionRequest
blocks.description: Creates an extraction request for full-form event data with all property values.

args.name: eventCollection
args.info: Specifies the name of the event collection to analyze.

args.name: timeframe
args.info: Refines the scope of events to be included in the analysis based on when the event occurred.

args.name: filters
args.info: Refines the scope of events to be included in the analysis based on event property values.

args.name: timezone
args.info: Assigns a timezone offset to relative timeframes.

args.name: email
args.info: If an email address is specified, an email will be sent to it when your extraction is ready for download. If email is not specified, your extraction will be processed synchronously and your data will be returned as JSON.

args.name: latest
args.info: An integer containing the number of most recent events to extract.

blocks.name: extractToCSV
blocks.description: Extract to CSV file

args.name: eventCollection
args.info: Specifies the name of the event collection to analyze.

args.name: timeframe
args.info: Refines the scope of events to be included in the analysis based on when the event occurred.

blocks.description: Create a new project in the organization.

args.name: name
args.info: Specifies the name of the project to be created.

args.name: users
args.info: Specifies users for the project. If any users supplied do not exist, the request will fail. You will receive an error indicating which users are invalid.

blocks.name: updateProject

args.name: name
args.info: Specifies the name of the project to be created.

args.name: users
args.info: Specifies users for the project. If any users supplied do not exist, the request will fail. You will receive an error indicating which users are invalid.

blocks.name: createAccessKey
blocks.description: Create a new API Key for the project.

args.name: name
args.info: A human readable name for the API Key. Limited to 256 characters.

args.name: isActive
args.info: A boolean that indicates if the key is currently active or revoked.

args.name: permitted
args.info: A list of high level actions this key can perform. Possible options: “writes”, “queries”, “saved_queries”, “cached_queries”, “datasets”, “schema”

args.name: options
args.info: An object containing more details about the key’s permitted and restricted functionality.

blocks.name: getAllAccessKeys
blocks.description: Retrieves a list of Access Keys.

blocks.name: getSingleAccessKey
blocks.description: Retrieves an Access Key definition.

blocks.name: updateAccessKey
blocks.description: Updates an Access Key.

args.name: name
args.info: A human readable name for the API Key. Limited to 256 characters.

args.name: isActive

args.name: permitted
args.info: A list of high level actions this key can perform. Possible options: “writes”, “queries”, “saved_queries”, “cached_queries”, “datasets”, “schema”

args.name: options
args.info: An object containing more details about the key’s permitted and restricted functionality.

blocks.name: revokeAccessKey
blocks.description: Revoking an Access Key.

blocks.name: unrevokeAccessKey
